<div class = "uk-padding" id = "popularity_col" style = "display:none">
<h3>Popularity</h3>

<center><img src= "{{=URL('static','images/user_guide/Pop_col_scheme.jpg')}}" alt="" style = "width:100%"></img></center>

<p> The leaf colours correspond to how popular the species is according to our {{=A('index of species popularity', _href=URL('popularity','index.html'))}}, which is calculated for every species in the tree. Popularity for a given species takes into account page length and page views for the English language Wikipedia entry of that species (if such a page exists) and also all the named groups (higher taxa to use the scientific term) containing that species.</p>

</div>


